many programs provide free health care and senior discounts, limited funds

make an adequate quality of health care very difficult to attain.

Despite recent changes in government recently bringing hundreds of millions of dollars to health care and long term care

services, there is still great need for improvement in waste management.

There are many simple ways to improve the issue of waste management. They include the following: introducing higher rates on waste

disposal, educating people and companies on what can be recycled and what not, setting up more recycling stations for the appropriaterecyclable materials, organizing and encouraging rewarding programs for healthy waste management, enforcing fines. The people here are not educated and hardly are any organizations and groups for us seniors to parttake in education.

The area of waste management has many possibilities of improvement. However,

before this is possible, more organizations and neighborhoods need to educate

on what can and cannot be recycled. Many people are simply ignorant on the

process of waste management. More people need to be made aware of the long term

consequences of littering and people not taking care of their waste accordingly.
